Package: ensemblelink
Title: Zero-Shot Record Linkage with Ensemble Retrieval and Cross-Encoder Reranking
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Noah", "Dasanaike", email = "noahdasanaike@g.harvard.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Performs fuzzy record linkage using ensemble retrieval (dense embeddings +
    sparse TF-IDF) combined with cross-encoder reranking. Requires no labeled training
    data and outperforms supervised methods on standard benchmarks. Uses Python backend
    via reticulate.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Imports:
    reticulate (>= 1.26)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.9), PyTorch, sentence-transformers, faiss-cpu or faiss-gpu
